by weaverryan at 2014-08-19T22:09:04Z

+1 for this, unless I'm missing some reason why we're enforcing this. This has always seemed a bit odd to me, and I've seen it make a few people unhappy recently :).

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

by fabpot at 2014-08-26T14:32:42Z

The convention is enforced on purpose. It allows to easily guess the config entry for any bundles, instead of having to look at the docs to figure it out. Of course, having this convention also allows tools (IDE, generators, checkers, ...) to also do their job easily. As already said, if you really insist on changing the default, you can still override the getExtension method.

:-1: for this change as I really think the current way is way better for end users. Removing it would be a regression in the DX IMO.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

